WEBVTT

00:02.000 --> 00:04.120
Dude, I really like
what you guys are doing down here.

00:04.120 --> 00:06.760
There is not as much
money in it as you think.

00:06.760 --> 00:08.200
But you and I could make money.

00:08.200 --> 00:09.880
If you love someone, you...

00:09.880 --> 00:11.360
..set them free.

00:11.360 --> 00:14.160
She is sex on legs. Speaking of.

00:14.160 --> 00:16.360
How's it going, Mr Colston?
Tania.

00:16.360 --> 00:18.280
You knew how I got the cashflow
to start Bare Feet.

00:18.280 --> 00:20.640
You knew what goes on in Bali.
What'd you think was happening

00:20.640 --> 00:22.120
when Buddy showed up?
This is bullshit!

00:22.120 --> 00:23.840
I've been watching young Dimma.

00:23.840 --> 00:25.800
I've been thinking
about putting him in the film.

00:25.800 --> 00:27.280
I'd love to take him to Indo.

00:27.280 --> 00:29.040
Reg, is this normal?
REG: This is far from normal.

00:29.040 --> 00:30.520
Just keep your head down.

00:30.520 --> 00:33.240
Look at this face.
Who's gonna stop this face?

00:33.240 --> 00:34.880
You don't know
what you're saying, Dim.

00:34.880 --> 00:36.640
SNAPPER: Let's go.

00:36.640 --> 00:39.200
You said two boards.
And yet there were three.

00:39.200 --> 00:40.200
Snap!

00:40.200 --> 00:42.360
Just keep walking.

00:49.000 --> 00:52.720
(WAVES LAP)

00:53.720 --> 00:56.720
(WAVES CRASH)

01:02.000 --> 01:04.920
(THUNDER CRASHES)

01:27.480 --> 01:32.080
BOY: (OUTSIDE) I'm gonna kill ya!
(INDISTINCT YELLING OUTSIDE)

01:44.320 --> 01:46.240
(BIRDS SQUAWK)

01:46.240 --> 01:49.960
PA: A requirement of all visitors
today to check in at the front desk

01:49.960 --> 01:52.800
and have their bags
checked and approved on entry.

01:52.800 --> 01:55.440
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

01:55.440 --> 01:57.680
Film's almost done.

01:58.880 --> 02:00.120
Mm.

02:00.120 --> 02:02.640
Sharpie reckons it looks
a bit straight, but he's, uh...

02:02.640 --> 02:04.360
..been tripping
a shitload of the green, so...

02:05.360 --> 02:07.600
..watch this space.

02:07.600 --> 02:09.840
He is talking to you then?

02:11.080 --> 02:12.280
No.

02:12.280 --> 02:13.760
No, he's not.

02:15.360 --> 02:17.040
You're in it, though.

02:18.040 --> 02:19.040
Dead set?

02:19.040 --> 02:20.560
Yeah, the whole Indo sequence.

02:20.560 --> 02:21.760
Apparently.

02:21.760 --> 02:25.080
It's mostly you and, uh...
mostly you and Bud.

02:26.080 --> 02:27.320
So...

02:37.160 --> 02:39.080
The cops been back?

02:43.760 --> 02:46.600
I just told them I don't know
the guys who gave me the stuff,

02:46.600 --> 02:48.320
just met them on the beach.

02:48.320 --> 02:49.840
They bought it.

02:50.840 --> 02:51.960
Yeah.

02:54.800 --> 02:56.320
Yeah. It's fair.

02:56.320 --> 02:58.120
It's good.

03:01.760 --> 03:04.080
We're all missing Win.

03:04.080 --> 03:05.520
(PUFFS)

03:07.680 --> 03:10.240
Not what she says about you.

03:11.240 --> 03:12.240
Hm.

03:13.240 --> 03:14.880
Yeah, I'm sorry she quit.

03:14.880 --> 03:17.320
She reckons if she stayed
in that town any longer...

03:18.320 --> 03:20.480
..she would've killed you.

03:23.720 --> 03:25.600
OK. (SIGHS)

03:25.600 --> 03:27.080
Um...

03:28.160 --> 03:31.440
You keep your nose clean,

03:31.440 --> 03:34.240
and I'll...I'll see you soon.

03:35.240 --> 03:36.480
OK?

03:45.080 --> 03:47.280
Trace.
Nope.

03:49.280 --> 03:50.800
Hey.

03:51.800 --> 03:53.600
Brought you some fruit.

04:02.040 --> 04:03.920
Ooh, it's looking good.

04:03.920 --> 04:05.480
Who's it for?

04:05.480 --> 04:07.560
Special commission.

04:07.560 --> 04:09.840
For Dimma.

04:16.560 --> 04:18.200
Snap been?

04:19.200 --> 04:21.440
Not my problem anymore.

04:27.800 --> 04:31.680
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

04:37.160 --> 04:39.200
Hey, hey.

04:40.200 --> 04:41.720
Do you want a drink?

04:42.720 --> 04:44.000
A smoke?

04:45.000 --> 04:47.920
Uh... No, I was thinking
of, um...getting an early night.

04:47.920 --> 04:49.840
Going for a surf tomorrow.

04:49.840 --> 04:52.400
You wanna come with me?

04:52.400 --> 04:54.120
Nah, I'm good.

04:57.760 --> 05:00.280
TROTTER: Well, is that the best
you can do for me?

05:01.280 --> 05:04.240
Well, who else buys
this amount of Velcro every month?

05:04.240 --> 05:06.680
(LAUGHS)

05:06.680 --> 05:08.120
No way.

05:08.120 --> 05:09.680
Well, come down on the weekend.

05:09.680 --> 05:11.360
Yeah, mornings have been perfect.

05:12.360 --> 05:14.760
Yeah,
you can just camp out the back here.

05:14.760 --> 05:16.640
OK. I'm done.
(LAUGHS)

05:16.640 --> 05:17.880
Great.

05:17.880 --> 05:20.880
No more excuses. It's about time
you got back in the water.

05:21.880 --> 05:24.240
Like a lazy seal. (LAUGHS)

05:24.240 --> 05:26.800
OK. Alright, bye.

05:27.800 --> 05:29.480
(LAUGHS)

05:29.480 --> 05:31.680
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.
No more calls.

05:32.680 --> 05:34.960
Hey, where are you going?

05:34.960 --> 05:37.200
Nowhere, just a little party.

05:37.200 --> 05:38.440
Great.

05:38.440 --> 05:40.240
It's at Bare Feet.

05:40.240 --> 05:41.520
Sorry!

05:41.520 --> 05:43.280
Traitor!

05:44.480 --> 05:47.160
(BIRD SQUAWKS)

05:47.160 --> 05:50.160
SONG: # A silent town

05:51.160 --> 05:54.800
# You've been around and found it

05:54.800 --> 05:57.880
# You took the wrong way in

05:58.960 --> 06:02.120
# Now tell me where you've been

06:03.480 --> 06:06.760
# Dark nights I've seen you

06:06.760 --> 06:11.800
# In cold streets
of tears and despair

06:14.320 --> 06:16.280
# And dawn

06:18.040 --> 06:20.400
# Is what you thought you saw

06:21.760 --> 06:24.520
# Nobody told you then

06:25.520 --> 06:28.480
# You'd never find a friend

06:30.200 --> 06:33.440
# All that you've been through

06:33.440 --> 06:35.640
# It feeds off you

06:35.640 --> 06:39.160
# Day after day... #

06:39.160 --> 06:40.560
DANI: I wouldn't.

06:41.560 --> 06:45.120
He's an amazing surfer
and off the drugs for now,

06:45.120 --> 06:48.520
but all that partying's
left him a bit...

06:51.840 --> 06:53.160
Beer?

06:54.160 --> 06:55.680
Mm-hm.

07:04.480 --> 07:07.120
(OWL HOOTS)

07:07.120 --> 07:10.720
(FIRE CRACKLES)

07:17.640 --> 07:20.640
(SNAPPER URINATES)

07:42.240 --> 07:45.040
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYS)

07:49.840 --> 07:53.080
(WATER LAPS)

07:58.360 --> 08:01.360
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYS)

08:25.840 --> 08:29.280
BUDDY: So, that's it,
your folks have really cut you off?

08:29.280 --> 08:32.040
HUNTER: Well, I have an idea.

08:33.040 --> 08:34.840
(PHONE RINGS)

08:34.840 --> 08:36.240
TRACY: Trot.

08:36.240 --> 08:38.320
(RINGING CONTINUES)

08:38.320 --> 08:39.440
Trot!

08:39.440 --> 08:41.520
What? Oh!

08:41.520 --> 08:46.760
(RINGING CONTINUES)

08:46.760 --> 08:48.440
Yeah?

08:48.440 --> 08:50.040
(PHONE LINE BEEPS)

08:50.040 --> 08:51.320
HUNTER: (ON PHONE) Trotter!

08:51.320 --> 08:52.880
Who's this?
Who do you think it is?

08:52.880 --> 08:54.640
What, did I wake you?

08:54.640 --> 08:57.240
Sorry. Buddy thought
he'd figured out the time difference.

08:57.240 --> 08:59.000
Oh, man, did I get it wrong?!

08:59.000 --> 09:01.080
It's all good, mate.
What's up? Is everything OK?

09:01.080 --> 09:03.760
Listen, Trot,
we'd like to make you an offer.

09:03.760 --> 09:09.880
Buddy and I would like to buy the
licence to sell Lightwave in the US.

09:09.880 --> 09:11.480
Yeah?

09:11.480 --> 09:13.600
Think about how awesome
it would be, Trot!

09:13.600 --> 09:16.560
The fact is we know this market.

09:16.560 --> 09:20.000
We're confident we could secure
much broader distribution,

09:20.000 --> 09:22.880
reach out to locals
we already have a relationship with.

09:22.880 --> 09:25.880
We give you 10% royalties
on everything we sell.

09:25.880 --> 09:27.880
Have you got the money for this,
Newport?

09:29.160 --> 09:33.080
I'm talking US Dollars, Trot.

09:33.080 --> 09:34.880
Lots of 'em.

09:35.880 --> 09:38.320
Let me sleep on it, eh?

09:38.320 --> 09:40.280
Yeah, that's all we ask.

09:40.280 --> 09:42.000
Right, no worries.

09:43.040 --> 09:45.000
What was that all about?

09:45.000 --> 09:46.760
America.

09:47.760 --> 09:51.640
(WAVES LAP, BIRD SQUAWKS)

09:51.640 --> 09:55.000
(CLATTERING)

10:02.760 --> 10:05.800
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

10:10.520 --> 10:12.600
(GRUNTS)

10:12.600 --> 10:16.120
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

10:17.560 --> 10:21.000
(WAVES LAP)

10:27.680 --> 10:33.000
(WAVE RUMBLES)

10:54.240 --> 10:55.720
Good morning.

10:55.720 --> 10:58.360
You're out early.
Yeah, couldn't sleep.

10:59.880 --> 11:02.720
I'm, uh...
thinking about taking a trip.

11:02.720 --> 11:04.360
An adventure?

11:04.360 --> 11:06.960
Where in the world
is Trotter off to now?

11:06.960 --> 11:09.240
Morocco? South America?

11:09.240 --> 11:10.600
California, actually.

11:10.600 --> 11:12.320
Oh, are you catching up
with the guys?

11:13.560 --> 11:16.200
Yeah, they wanna give Lightwave
a go in the US.

11:16.200 --> 11:18.360
You'd give them your baby?

11:18.360 --> 11:20.000
Nah, just the licence.

11:20.000 --> 11:22.040
(SIGHS) Hunter's got a good head
on his shoulders,

11:22.040 --> 11:24.720
but Buddy...I don't know.
Yeah, I know.

11:24.720 --> 11:28.680
But...you know,
people love him, he rips.

11:28.680 --> 11:31.240
I've been trying to get him
to do a campaign for us for months.

11:31.240 --> 11:34.000
And now they want to steal your idea
for themselves, huh?

11:35.400 --> 11:36.680
Do you think?

11:37.880 --> 11:39.440
What do I know?

11:40.680 --> 11:42.560
Hey, maybe
you'll become a millionaire

11:42.560 --> 11:44.560
and never have to leave home.

11:44.560 --> 11:46.520
Isn't that the dream?

12:04.520 --> 12:06.400
Passport.

12:06.400 --> 12:07.920
Ticket.

12:08.920 --> 12:10.560
Ah, shit, don't tell me I forgot.

12:12.960 --> 12:14.160
Thanks.

12:15.160 --> 12:18.320
Let me know
if there's anything else you need.

12:19.320 --> 12:21.480
You alright?
Fine.

12:21.480 --> 12:23.240
Don't say 'fine'.

12:23.240 --> 12:24.480
What? I am fine.

12:24.480 --> 12:26.880
You're saying 'fine' like women say
when they're NOT fine.

12:26.880 --> 12:29.640
Oh, so now it's about women
collectively as an issue, is it?

12:29.640 --> 12:32.400
This is you and me. Talk to me.

12:32.400 --> 12:35.360
Did you even think once
about asking me to come?

12:35.360 --> 12:37.640
Trace.
We started this business together.

12:37.640 --> 12:39.360
How come you're the one
going to America?

12:39.360 --> 12:41.080
It's not like that.

12:41.080 --> 12:42.760
And you're gonna miss my birthday.

12:42.760 --> 12:44.520
And I am so sorry about that,

12:44.520 --> 12:46.800
but we really can't afford
two international airfares.

12:46.800 --> 12:48.600
So, how come I'm working two jobs?

12:48.600 --> 12:52.160
Well...if you don't wanna work
two jobs, quit one.

12:52.160 --> 12:53.440
Ha!

12:53.440 --> 12:55.520
You're happy for me to quit school?

12:55.520 --> 12:56.800
Great.

12:56.800 --> 12:59.600
That place is doing my head in,
you know?

12:59.600 --> 13:01.880
Even though it feels
like I'm the only person in there

13:01.880 --> 13:03.400
who gives a shit about the kids,

13:03.400 --> 13:05.600
I could quit tomorrow.

13:05.600 --> 13:07.040
So soon?

13:07.040 --> 13:08.520
Trot.
(CHUCKLES)

13:09.920 --> 13:13.400
Look, I know you're over it,

13:13.400 --> 13:15.480
but, you quit now,

13:15.480 --> 13:18.080
that's even more reason we can't
afford two international flights.

13:19.080 --> 13:20.480
You serious?

13:21.800 --> 13:23.400
Trace!

13:27.440 --> 13:29.200
Have a safe trip, Trot.

13:29.200 --> 13:30.880
Hey, come on. Trace!

13:31.880 --> 13:33.120
Really?!

13:35.160 --> 13:38.160
(BREATHES RAPIDLY)

13:52.520 --> 13:54.880
Turn on and tune in, mate!

15:03.880 --> 15:11.520
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

15:19.840 --> 15:21.400
Hand it over.

15:21.400 --> 15:23.280
Can we get it back after class?
No.

15:23.280 --> 15:25.240
But, Miss!
Ask me again, Choc.

15:25.240 --> 15:27.080
I double-dare you.

15:27.080 --> 15:29.720
CLASS: Ooh!

15:29.720 --> 15:33.120
(LAUGHTER)
Just go back to your work, OK?

15:34.120 --> 15:37.280
Tania Sanderson, my office,
immediately.

15:37.280 --> 15:39.520
CLASS: Ooh!

15:40.680 --> 15:42.320
What's going on, Mr Colston?

15:42.320 --> 15:44.600
That's for Miss Sanderson and I
to discuss, actually, Mrs Dwyer,

15:44.600 --> 15:45.600
thank you.

15:45.600 --> 15:48.760
I believe she's well aware
of the issue at hand. Come on.

15:54.360 --> 15:57.400
SNAPPER:
So, Wizard, can you help me out?

15:57.400 --> 15:59.000
WIZARD: I don't know, man.

16:00.000 --> 16:02.120
You know, I've tried
to leave that scene behind.

16:03.480 --> 16:04.880
Yeah.

16:04.880 --> 16:07.040
Yeah, course. Mm.

16:07.040 --> 16:08.520
And I'm not suggesting

16:08.520 --> 16:10.400
that you'll need to get involved
or anything,

16:10.400 --> 16:12.120
um...it's just...

16:12.120 --> 16:15.440
..if you...if you knew anybody
from back in the day

16:15.440 --> 16:18.600
that might be, uh...keen.

16:29.920 --> 16:33.240
There's a guy. In Sydney.

16:34.240 --> 16:36.360
If he's still around.

16:37.920 --> 16:39.880
Great.

16:39.880 --> 16:40.880
Yeah.

16:40.880 --> 16:43.160
That's a dark space, though,
Snapper.

16:44.160 --> 16:47.160
He casts a toxic shadow.

16:47.160 --> 16:48.760
Well, it's good stuff.

16:48.760 --> 16:50.320
Like, well,
actually I got it from,...

16:50.320 --> 16:52.800
Oh, I don't wanna hear it, man.

16:53.960 --> 16:56.160
You carry your shit...

16:57.160 --> 16:59.200
..I'll carry mine.

17:04.920 --> 17:07.360
So, you will hook me up?

17:07.360 --> 17:09.520
I'll get you a name.

17:16.880 --> 17:19.680
(ENGINE ROARS)

17:19.680 --> 17:23.320
('HI HONEY HO' BY DADDY COOL PLAYS)

17:34.280 --> 17:36.280
SONG: # Honey, hi

17:37.480 --> 17:40.000
# Mm, honey, ho

17:41.240 --> 17:43.640
# How are you?!

17:44.800 --> 17:46.480
# Oh, baby!

17:46.480 --> 17:49.880
# Workin' can kill a man

17:49.880 --> 17:54.240
# Lovin' babes like you can too

18:00.360 --> 18:04.320
# Uh, huh, honey, hi!

18:04.320 --> 18:07.920
# Oh, honey, ho!

18:07.920 --> 18:09.560
# Shake it, break it

18:09.560 --> 18:11.840
# Oh, for goodness sake, I

