# Love the way we carry on

18:22.080 --> 18:23.880
# And on

18:23.880 --> 18:26.000
# And on

18:26.000 --> 18:29.440
# And on and on and on and on

18:29.440 --> 18:32.520
# Uh, huh, honey, hi!

18:33.520 --> 18:36.840
# Oh, ho, honey, ho!

18:36.840 --> 18:38.760
# Yeah! Honey! Whoo! #

18:42.760 --> 18:44.720
(WAVES CRASH)

18:44.720 --> 18:46.400
TROTTER: You've improved, Newbie.

18:46.400 --> 18:47.880
BUDDY: Ah, the waves
are kinder here.

18:47.880 --> 18:49.560
HUNTER: Ah, well,
practice makes perfect.

18:49.560 --> 18:51.560
I never said perfect.

18:51.560 --> 18:53.280
I miss how Australians give you shit

18:53.280 --> 18:55.480
to show you
how much they really care.

18:55.480 --> 18:59.280
I tell you what, Trot...why don't
you and I go and grab some beers

18:59.280 --> 19:02.640
and, uh...go take a look
over these, uh...licence numbers?

19:02.640 --> 19:04.840
Yeah, about that. Um...

19:05.920 --> 19:08.160
Look, I don't want you guys
to take this the wrong way,

19:08.160 --> 19:10.120
but I was thinking, while I'm here,

19:10.120 --> 19:12.440
I might go see a few people myself.

19:12.440 --> 19:13.600
What do you mean?

19:13.600 --> 19:16.880
Well...you know I love you guys,
but...

19:16.880 --> 19:19.880
..I can't just give Lightwave
to you.

19:20.920 --> 19:23.040
No, obviously we'd pay for it.

19:23.040 --> 19:24.520
No, I know what the deal is,

19:24.520 --> 19:28.200
but I was thinking, since I'm here,
why don't I give it a go myself?

19:30.520 --> 19:32.680
Yeah, sure, that makes sense.

19:32.680 --> 19:34.600
Go for it, man.

19:38.160 --> 19:40.280
Can I borrow your car?

19:42.600 --> 19:45.600
O-m-m-m-m-m.

19:45.600 --> 19:50.920
(CHANTS)

19:55.560 --> 19:58.360
(CONTINUES CHANTING)

19:58.360 --> 19:59.760
(SIGHS)

20:10.640 --> 20:11.640
Namaste.

20:18.880 --> 20:19.880
Hi.

20:21.440 --> 20:24.200
Jules. From the party.

20:25.320 --> 20:26.320
Hey.

20:26.320 --> 20:28.720
So, how long you been doing yoga?

20:28.720 --> 20:31.520
On and off for a few years, I guess.

20:31.520 --> 20:33.280
Help with your surfing?

20:33.280 --> 20:34.800
Yeah, it's a trip.

20:34.800 --> 20:37.440
I mean, most activity
connected to the body

20:37.440 --> 20:39.320
affects what happens in the water.

20:40.320 --> 20:42.200
That's why
I don't engage in intercourse.

20:43.600 --> 20:45.400
Sorry...what?

20:45.400 --> 20:49.520
You need to maintain
an opening to kundalini awakening.

20:51.200 --> 20:55.600
Keeping the mula bandha
as a sacred space

20:55.600 --> 20:58.960
connects me more deeply to Lir,
the sea god.

21:01.040 --> 21:02.640
You dig it?

21:04.560 --> 21:06.360
Oh, absolutely.

21:09.840 --> 21:12.320
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

21:12.320 --> 21:14.920
(SQUEAKING)

21:14.920 --> 21:17.480
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

21:32.800 --> 21:34.840
It's like a ray of light, you see?

21:34.840 --> 21:37.160
How the colours
refract through the wave?

21:37.160 --> 21:38.800
Yeah, my wife came up with that.

21:38.800 --> 21:42.000
I'm Bill Dwyer. I'm here
representing Lightwave board shorts.

21:42.000 --> 21:43.360
We've got a factory
right on the beach.

21:43.360 --> 21:45.040
These guys are being made
out of a little surf town

21:45.040 --> 21:46.520
in Australia called Woogonga.

21:46.520 --> 21:48.800
Oh, it's the best pair
of board shorts you'll ever wear.

21:48.800 --> 21:51.000
WOMAN: Say it again?
(CHUCKLES)

21:51.000 --> 21:53.080
Board shorts.
Again.

21:53.080 --> 21:54.440
Board shorts.

21:54.440 --> 21:56.720
They're quick-drying,
perfect length,

21:56.720 --> 21:59.640
designed by surfers for surfers.

22:04.120 --> 22:05.240
Not bad.

22:05.240 --> 22:07.400
Kids are going crazy for them
back in Australia.

22:09.880 --> 22:12.880
So...do we have a deal?

22:12.880 --> 22:14.960
Congratulations, man.
Bravo, man.

22:14.960 --> 22:16.840
Cheers. Cheers.
You really killed them, huh?

22:16.840 --> 22:18.120
Mm.

22:18.120 --> 22:21.480
Thank you. Thank you.
I mean, clean sweep.

22:21.480 --> 22:25.400
Eastern Sun, The Wave, Surf
and Vibes, they all want a piece.

22:25.400 --> 22:27.680
That's really great!

22:27.680 --> 22:30.480
I might call Trace,
give her the good news.

22:33.320 --> 22:34.840
Should we tell him?

22:34.840 --> 22:37.680
Nah, man, there's no rush.

22:38.680 --> 22:41.600
(PHONE RINGS)

22:44.360 --> 22:46.680
(RINGING CONTINUES)

22:46.680 --> 22:48.320
(PHONE LINE RINGS)

22:48.320 --> 22:50.680
Come on, babe.
(SCHOOL BELL RINGS)

22:50.680 --> 22:52.640
TRACY: Alright, see you tomorrow!
STUDENT: See ya.

22:52.640 --> 22:54.440
See you!

22:56.440 --> 22:58.440
(SIGHS)

23:01.120 --> 23:02.760
Jesus Christ.

23:13.240 --> 23:16.240
(BREATHES SHAKILY)

23:25.520 --> 23:27.000
MAN: Hey!

23:27.000 --> 23:28.280
Hey, man!

23:28.280 --> 23:30.160
Who the fuck do you think you are?!

23:30.160 --> 23:31.720
Whoa, hey, sorry, I didn't...

23:31.720 --> 23:33.120
Sorry. Ohh! Jeez!

23:33.120 --> 23:35.360
You sold to me and
then every other store on the strip?

23:35.360 --> 23:38.240
Hey, Fox! Fox!
Come on, man, be cool!

23:38.240 --> 23:39.920
(GROANS) Who the hell

23:39.920 --> 23:41.600
do you think you are, you clown?
Trotter, just...

23:41.600 --> 23:43.440
Trotter, don't push it, OK?

23:43.440 --> 23:45.440
Don't come near my shop again!

23:45.440 --> 23:49.160
Guys on the Cali scene,
they don't mess around.

23:49.160 --> 23:51.120
It's a dog-eat-dog town.

23:51.120 --> 23:53.680
Oh, and they don't really dig
strangers on their turf.

23:53.680 --> 23:55.400
Yeah, but they all closed deals.

23:55.400 --> 23:57.720
Right, and they thought
that you were just selling to them.

23:57.720 --> 24:01.320
Dude, you see the way
we name beaches?

24:01.320 --> 24:04.120
One block on
is a totally different crew.

24:04.120 --> 24:06.080
I mean,
once you get in good with one shop,

24:06.080 --> 24:09.640
kinda eliminates
you from all the rest.

24:09.640 --> 24:11.200
It's very tribal.

24:11.200 --> 24:12.600
Tribal?

24:13.840 --> 24:16.520
And you two knew all along,
didn't you?

24:16.520 --> 24:18.000
Arseholes.
(PHONE RINGS)

24:18.000 --> 24:19.960
Ooh, that'll be about my audition.

24:19.960 --> 24:21.880
Hey, good luck!

24:21.880 --> 24:23.840
Our offer still stands.

24:23.840 --> 24:25.880
Is this more California mafia shit?

24:25.880 --> 24:27.840
Am I gonna end up
buried in the desert?

24:27.840 --> 24:29.400
Well, only if you ask nicely.

24:29.400 --> 24:31.600
Let us take over
the US licence of Lightwave,

24:31.600 --> 24:32.920
save yourself the headache.

24:32.920 --> 24:35.720
No offence, but I really
don't see Buddy as a businessman.

24:35.720 --> 24:37.000
None taken.

24:37.000 --> 24:39.840
And as for you, Newbie,
mm, I don't know.

24:40.840 --> 24:42.520
Not salty by nature.

24:47.520 --> 24:49.640
You give us this chance...

24:50.640 --> 24:52.880
..I have no doubt
we can make this happen for you.

24:52.880 --> 24:55.400
You just hung me out to dry,

24:55.400 --> 24:57.960
so why would I trust
anything you say?

24:59.400 --> 25:01.000
Is that a no?

25:03.360 --> 25:04.560
Dude...

25:05.560 --> 25:09.000
..do you even know
how close we are to Mexico?

25:11.000 --> 25:13.160
All these bad vibes...

25:13.160 --> 25:15.880
..can't start anything like this,
huh?

25:15.880 --> 25:17.800
You know what we need?

25:17.800 --> 25:19.120
Road trip.

25:19.120 --> 25:21.320
(SCOFFS)
(CHORTLES)

25:22.680 --> 25:24.800
They gave the part to Nancy Lopez.

25:24.800 --> 25:26.000
Again.

25:26.000 --> 25:27.440
Oh, babe!

25:27.440 --> 25:29.120
Hey, I'm so sorry.

25:29.120 --> 25:30.240
Oh.

25:30.240 --> 25:32.880
They gave me
the friend part instead.

25:32.880 --> 25:34.680
Wait, the waitress?!

25:34.680 --> 25:36.520
Oh! That's badass!

25:36.520 --> 25:39.080
You think?
Yeah! That's so much better! Oh!

25:39.080 --> 25:41.920
Eh! Eh. You can't say no now.

25:41.920 --> 25:45.360
The universe, it's on a roll, baby!
Huh?

25:45.360 --> 25:48.480
(CHANTS) Road trip! Road trip!
Road trip! Road trip!

25:48.480 --> 25:51.360
Oh, my God! My little star!

25:51.360 --> 25:53.240
Oh, yeah!

26:13.400 --> 26:16.160
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

26:16.160 --> 26:17.440
(GRUNTS)

26:17.440 --> 26:20.520
Hey, gook!
Maybe he didn't hear you.

26:20.520 --> 26:21.600
Chink!

26:25.320 --> 26:26.640
(GROANS)

26:29.840 --> 26:30.840
(GRUNTS)

26:36.920 --> 26:39.120
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

26:39.120 --> 26:41.240
(SCHOOL BELL RINGS)

26:41.240 --> 26:44.160
(CHATTER, LAUGHTER)

26:44.160 --> 26:47.360
MR LOCKWOOD: Enter!
(LAUGHTER)

26:47.360 --> 26:49.640
Ah! Ha. Mrs Dwyer.

26:51.400 --> 26:52.920
Mr Lockwood.

26:52.920 --> 26:54.720
Take a seat.

26:57.040 --> 26:59.760
Now, I think it's important

26:59.760 --> 27:03.200
that we all agree to discuss
the issue at hand as adults.

27:03.200 --> 27:04.520
MR COLSTON: Yep.

27:04.520 --> 27:06.920
Mr Colston, if you'd like to begin?

27:06.920 --> 27:10.520
Yeah. Uh... Look, I guess, um...

27:10.520 --> 27:14.600
..best guess is that she's got some
kind of schoolgirl crush, you know?

27:14.600 --> 27:17.000
It's not the first time, certainly
not the last time it's gonna happen.

27:17.000 --> 27:19.240
It doesn't mean
you have to actively encourage her.

27:19.240 --> 27:22.040
Pulled her aside, had a little chat,
that's it. Set her straight.

27:24.440 --> 27:26.200
Fred, I can't be held responsible

27:26.200 --> 27:28.800
for some
silly little teenage fantasy.

27:28.800 --> 27:30.440
Hm.

27:31.440 --> 27:33.840
Does this fantasy
involve your dick in her mouth?

27:33.840 --> 27:36.320
Oh, that's...
Mrs Dwyer, language, please.

27:36.320 --> 27:38.480
This is a place of learning.
Exactly.

27:38.480 --> 27:39.960
Which is why I like to draw a line

27:39.960 --> 27:43.400
on young women being removed from
my classroom and taken advantage of.

27:43.400 --> 27:46.160
I think it's a bit ripe,
risking my reputation

27:46.160 --> 27:48.600
on the sort of girl who's been
around the block a couple of times.

27:48.600 --> 27:50.640
I saw you, Ricky.

27:51.640 --> 27:55.200
Honestly, I've got no idea
why you would make this story up!

27:55.200 --> 27:57.560
I've no idea.
I thought we were professionals.

27:57.560 --> 27:59.280
Mr Lockwood...
Yeah, alright, Mrs Dwyer.

27:59.280 --> 28:01.760
I think you've made your vehemence
quite clear.

28:02.760 --> 28:05.880
Now, I appreciate
you both giving your time today

28:05.880 --> 28:08.160
and I can assure you
that this unfortunate matter

28:08.160 --> 28:09.640
will be dealt with immediately.

28:11.600 --> 28:13.000
Thank you.

28:18.440 --> 28:19.680
(JULES GASPS)

28:19.680 --> 28:21.680
(PUFFS)
Sorry!

28:21.680 --> 28:23.560
You are kidding me!

28:23.560 --> 28:25.520
(LAUGHS) Come on!

28:31.680 --> 28:33.560
BUDDY:
Hey, you remember last time, Hunter?

28:33.560 --> 28:36.160
HUNTER: Oh, yeah, all too well.
(LAUGHS)

28:36.160 --> 28:38.280
TROTTER: What happened last time?
Oh, we can't talk about it.

28:38.280 --> 28:40.440
Yeah, we should go there.

28:40.440 --> 28:42.120
Let's go create our own memories.

28:42.120 --> 28:44.360
Can you hold that for me? Thank you.

28:44.360 --> 28:47.160
Hey, Trot, chuck us the map.
Glovebox.

28:48.160 --> 28:49.360
Whoa!

28:51.440 --> 28:53.080
Come on, man,

28:53.080 --> 28:55.200
we're going to Mexico.

28:55.200 --> 28:57.320
(ENGINE STARTS)

29:02.080 --> 29:03.480
Let's go!

29:04.480 --> 29:05.760
Ooh!

29:05.760 --> 29:07.800
(BARRY SIGHS)

29:08.800 --> 29:11.440
So, is Trot still in America?

29:11.440 --> 29:12.440
Mm-hm.

29:12.440 --> 29:14.720
Mm-hm. Yeah.

29:14.720 --> 29:18.200
I always wanted to go
to the Grand Canyon. (CHUCKLES)

29:18.200 --> 29:20.000
Is he anywhere near there?

29:20.000 --> 29:22.320
MARGAUX:
Actually, he's in Laguna Beach.

29:22.320 --> 29:24.840
The Grand Canyon is in Arizona.

29:24.840 --> 29:26.720
It's about 600 miles away.

29:26.720 --> 29:28.360
Oh, right.

29:29.360 --> 29:31.760
Bigger than you think, isn't it?
It is.

29:31.760 --> 29:34.200
I will have a red wine,
please, Barry.

29:34.200 --> 29:36.360
Tracy?
I'm OK.

29:36.360 --> 29:39.120
One red wine coming up.

29:41.440 --> 29:43.480
So...

29:43.480 --> 29:46.280
..it must be tough for you
with Trotter away.

29:47.280 --> 29:48.760
I don't know.

29:48.760 --> 29:50.640
Less dirty things
to pick up off the floor, I guess.

29:50.640 --> 29:52.840
No, men only think of themselves.

29:52.840 --> 29:54.640
There you go.
Thanks.

29:54.640 --> 29:57.560
Sharpie just smokes weed
and edits his film

29:57.560 --> 30:01.080
over and over again
and all night, all day.

30:02.560 --> 30:07.520
And every time
I see Dimma in the footage,

30:07.520 --> 30:10.840
after everything that happened,
it's...it's...

30:10.840 --> 30:12.640
..it's heartbreaking.

30:15.560 --> 30:17.040
My brother being in that film

30:17.040 --> 30:20.200
is one of the things
keeping him alive right now.

30:21.200 --> 30:23.160
We're grateful.

30:27.960 --> 30:29.920
So, how is Trotter going?

30:31.600 --> 30:34.200
I've hardly heard. (CHUCKLES)

30:34.200 --> 30:36.600
Says he can't work out
the time difference.

30:36.600 --> 30:39.760
Oh, so he's smart enough
to start Lightwave US for himself,

30:39.760 --> 30:42.520
but can't figure out
how to use a payphone? (SCOFFS)

30:42.520 --> 30:44.480
It's just the licence, actually.

30:45.480 --> 30:46.640
Oh.

30:46.640 --> 30:48.880
I must've misunderstood him.

30:48.880 --> 30:50.320
Yeah.

30:51.440 --> 30:53.080
You know Trot -

30:53.080 --> 30:56.800
always making things out
to be bigger than they are.

31:00.320 --> 31:04.360
PA: Visiting hours are 3:00 to 4:00
Tuesdays and Thursdays.

31:04.360 --> 31:07.080
If you need to arrange
an appointment outside that time

31:07.080 --> 31:09.640
please contact the guards
at reception.

31:13.440 --> 31:15.320
Jesus, mate.

31:16.320 --> 31:18.000
DIMMA: Yeah.

31:26.200 --> 31:27.920
I don't smoke.

31:29.000 --> 31:32.400
Think of them more as, uh...
dollar bills.

31:34.240 --> 31:35.240
Ah.

31:38.120 --> 31:40.400
I saw Tracy.

31:42.880 --> 31:46.600
I think she's worried
about you getting scurvy.

31:53.360 --> 31:55.600
How're you goin'?

31:55.600 --> 31:57.920
I've been better.

31:59.040 --> 32:01.160
It'll be over soon.

32:03.320 --> 32:04.720
Will it?

32:05.760 --> 32:07.240
What if I don't get off?

32:08.440 --> 32:10.440
Well, then you do the time

32:10.440 --> 32:12.560
and you keep your head down.

32:13.560 --> 32:16.000
There's no point being a hero.

32:18.320 --> 32:20.000
One thing I know...

32:21.000 --> 32:22.840
..you can't do this solo.

32:25.720 --> 32:28.600
Make some friends,
but not the white kids,

32:28.600 --> 32:31.320
they're never gonna be on your side,
do you hear me?

32:31.320 --> 32:32.320
Mm-hm.

32:39.640 --> 32:41.600
(STIFLES SOB)
(SOFTLY) Hey.

32:44.240 --> 32:46.120
Not in here, mate.

32:47.960 --> 32:50.480
You've gotta keep that shit inside.

32:59.120 --> 33:02.120
(WATER LAPS)

33:23.680 --> 33:25.160
Alright, Reg?

33:27.520 --> 33:29.680
(GRUNTS) What have you done?!

33:30.680 --> 33:34.440
Hey! What the hell?! What the hell?!
(GRUNTS)

33:35.680 --> 33:38.400
(WATER SPLASHES)

33:46.600 --> 33:48.280
TRACY: Tania.

33:48.280 --> 33:49.840
G'day, Mrs Dwyer.

33:49.840 --> 33:52.760
How are things?
Yeah, good.

33:52.760 --> 33:56.760
You weren't in class yesterday.
Had to see the headmaster.

33:56.760 --> 33:58.960
I heard there was some trouble
with Mr Colston?

33:59.960 --> 34:01.120
Who's been talking?

34:01.120 --> 34:02.600
No-one.

34:02.600 --> 34:04.680
It's just between us.

34:06.560 --> 34:09.680
You know you won't get in trouble
for telling the truth, right?

34:09.680 --> 34:11.440
There's nothing to tell.

34:12.600 --> 34:14.680
You don't owe Mr Colston anything.

34:14.680 --> 34:16.640
Mr Colston is just a friend.

34:16.640 --> 34:21.200
I mean...not like a friend. I guess
I sorta had a crush on him for a bit.

34:21.200 --> 34:24.360
But it was all just in my head,
you know?

34:27.040 --> 34:29.360
Is that what you told Mr Lockwood?

34:29.360 --> 34:30.640
Yep.

34:31.680 --> 34:35.160
And what did he say?
That the matter was closed.

34:36.680 --> 34:39.120
Tania, you're a bright girl.

34:39.120 --> 34:40.760
You can do anything you want.

34:40.760 --> 34:43.200
I know,
that's why I'm leaving school.

34:43.200 --> 34:45.320
I can get more shifts here.

34:47.320 --> 34:49.040
If that's what YOU want.

34:49.040 --> 34:52.320
It's better to save up
and get a car, isn't it?

34:52.320 --> 34:54.920
Or a holiday or something?

34:54.920 --> 34:56.640
School's a waste of time.

